{"instruction": "Explain the phenomenon of gradient explosion in training LSTM networks.","context":"","response": "Gradient explosion occurs when the gradients in the network become too large during backpropagation, leading to unstable training and divergence of the model parameters."}
{"instruction": "Explain the concept of query, key, and value in the context of attention mechanism.","context":"","response":"In attention mechanism, the query is used to determine which parts of the input sequence to focus on, the key is used to compute the similarity between the query and each part of the input sequence, and the value is the information associated with each key."}
{"instruction": "Explain the concept of few-shot zero-shot learning and how it combines the strengths of both approaches.", "context": "", "response": "Few-shot zero-shot learning combines the strengths of few-shot learning and zero-shot learning by using a small number of labeled examples for seen classes and leveraging semantic relationships or attributes to generalize to unseen classes, improving model performance on both seen and unseen classes."}
{"instruction": "How does self-attention mechanism help in capturing long-range dependencies in sequences?","context":"","response":"Self-attention mechanism helps in capturing long-range dependencies by allowing the model to attend to different parts of the input sequence based on their relevance to each other, enabling it to learn relationships between distant tokens."}
