{"instruction": "What are the limitations of cost functions in business decision-making? Discuss at least three limitations with examples.","context":"","response":"Three limitations of cost functions in business decision-making are: 1) They may oversimplify the cost structure by assuming linear relationships between cost and output. For example, in reality, costs may not change proportionally with output levels. 2) Cost functions may not account for external factors such as changes in market demand or input prices, leading to inaccurate cost estimates. 3) Cost functions may not capture the full complexity of production processes, such as interdependencies between different production stages, resulting in incomplete cost analysis."}
